There will be repeat broadcasts on Tuesday at 8pm and Saturday, December 2 at 3pm. South Africans have been encouraged to vote for Miss South Africa Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters ahead of the competition which takes place at The Axis in Las Vegas on Sunday. Pre-voting is open until November 25, the day before the pageant. There will also be a vote during the live broadcast for each round of the competition. The voting windows will happen during the actual competition so fans need to be ready to cast their ballots. Ahead of the pageant, South Africans can vote two ways: Go to Vote.MissUniverse.com - each person can vote 10 times a day. Vote on Twitter using both #MissUniverse #SouthAfrica (retweets count). During the live broadcast, vote in the same way. - Staff Reporter